  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Target one creature he can see within 30 feet of it and against which it has sworn vengeance. The target must make a DC 15 Wisdom saving throw. On a failure, the target is paralyzed until is creature deals damage to it, or until the end of this creature's next turn.</p>\n<p>When the paralysis ends, the target is frightened of the caster for 1 minute. The frightened target can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, with disadvantage if it can see the source of its fear, ending the frightened condition on itself on a success.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>FoundryVTT</strong>: This is spell will force the target to save and apply a one round paralasis effect. If the target is damaged by the caster the effect should be dropped and 1 minute of @JournalEntry[tjg0x0jXlwvbdI9h]{Frightened} added.</p>",
